title: What Catherine, Princess of Wales, says between the lines in her video
description: Royal watchers say Catherine, Princess of Wales, shared more than just her cancer diagnosis in the two-minute video.

title: Five holy events and holidays are packed into late March. Here’s why.
description: Five festivals or holy times from different cultures and religions are happening in late March: Holi, Nowruz, Easter, Purim and Ramadan. Here’s why and what to know.

title: What to know about Islamic State group, which claimed the Moscow attack
description: Islamic State group claimed responsibility for Friday’s attack in Moscow. Its Islamic State-Khorasan branch, known as ISIS-K, was active inside Russia, U.S. officials said.

title: Outpourings of support, calls for privacy after Princess Catherine cancer news
description: Support has poured in for Catherine, Princess of Wales after she revealed Friday she had been diagnosed with cancer, with many calling for her privacy to be respected.

title: Budget deal slashes U.S. funding for Palestinians’ U.N. lifeline
description: The federal spending package approved by Congress strips hundreds of millions of dollars from UNRWA, the U.N. agency that distributes most aid to Palestinians.

title: U.N. chief to visit Egypt’s border with Gaza as Netanyahu vows Rafah invasion
description: The U.N. Security Council failed to pass a U.S.-led cease-fire resolution. Israel’s Netanayhu pledged a ground invasion of Rafah despite U.S. warnings.

title: As its workers stream to the U.S., Mexico runs short of farmhands
description: Mexico seemed to have an inexhaustible supply of farmworkers. Thanks to globalization, it’s running short. Now employers are calling for guest workers.

title: Princess of Wales faces cancer diagnosis: A timeline of key events
description: Health struggles have kept the British royal family in the spotlight since the last official appearance at Christmas by Catherine, Princess of Wales.

title: U.S. warnings preceded deadly Moscow attack; ISIS claims responsibility
description: The attack, which killed more than 60 people, comes after the U.S. government warned it had information suggesting risk of a “planned terrorist attack in Moscow.”

title: What to know about Senegal’s wide-open elections
description: Neither incumbent Macky Sall nor rival Ousmane Sonko is on the ballot in Senegal’s presidential election Sunday.

title: Maduro’s strongest challenger, barred from running, picks a stand-in
description: María Corina Machado, who won a Venezuelan opposition presidential primary with 92 percent of the vote, called Corina Yori “an honorable person whom I trust.”
